      • translate

        public static java.lang.String translate(char[] dict)
        Translates a char array of numbers into letters based on the encodings put inside of the mapping called LetterEncodings.
        Parameters:
        char[] - dict Accepts the combined cube fragments 　@return String output The returned string is a translation of the numbers into letters.

      • createDict

        public static void createDict(java.io.File dictionary)
        Creates a dictionary of words translated to numbers. This is done by taking each entry in a text file and mapping each letter to its LetterEncodings and putting them in a SortedMap called map.
        Parameters:
        File - dictionary Text file of dictionary terms.

      • confirm

        public static boolean confirm(char[] dict,
                              char[] numb)
        Confirm essentially determines if there is a matching between phone numbers and translated text.
        Parameters:
        char[] - dict, char[] numb dict represents the translated text to numbers. numb represents the phone number that is being matched.
        Returns:
        true or false If a matching is found true is returned. Otherwise, false is returned.

      • Lookup

        public static void Lookup(java.lang.String num,
                          java.lang.String match,
                          java.lang.String original)
        Lookup essentially takes each phone number and attempts to find a matching within the SortedMap called map.
        Parameters:
        String - num, String match, String original num represents the phone number that is being matched. match stores a copy of a dictionary word if a match is found original is the dictionary unmodified

      • filterPrefix

        public static <V> java.util.SortedMap<java.lang.String,V> filterPrefix(java.util.SortedMap<java.lang.String,V> baseMap,
                                                                       java.lang.String prefix)
        filterPrefix essentially runs a partial search on SortedMap map to find any keys that contain references to the String prefix.
        Parameters:
        SortedMap - V> baseMap, String prefix baseMap is the SortedMap that will contain the submappings of the prefix's first character all the way to the end(entire String of prefix). prefix is the String that will be searched for inside of baseMap.
        Returns:
        SortedMap A list of keys from SortedMap map that contain references to prefix
